## System Role Assignments

All authorized break-glass users will also receive:

| Role | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| ACCOUNTADMIN | Emergency account administration |
| SECURITYADMIN | Grant management (use instead of ACCOUNTADMIN) |
| SYSADMIN | Object management (use instead of ACCOUNTADMIN) |

## Actions Generated

| # | Action | Details |
|---|--------|---------|
| 1 | Discover | Query current ACCOUNTADMIN holders |
| 2 | Grant | Ensure authorized users have ACCOUNTADMIN |
| 3 | Revoke | Generate REVOKE statements for unauthorized holders |
| 4 | Support Roles | Grant SECURITYADMIN + SYSADMIN to authorized users |

## Important Notes

- REVOKE statements are generated as **output** (not auto-executed) to prevent accidental lockout
- Review the Step 3 query output carefully before executing any REVOKE statements
- Ensure at least one authorized user can access the account before revoking others
- All authorized users should have MFA enabled

## Next Steps

After enforcing admin separation:
- Execute the generated REVOKE statements
- Configure ACCOUNTADMIN usage alerts (Task 4, Step 4.2)
- Document break-glass procedures in your runbook
